snippet: Only 27 players — and no headliners — are competing in the Tournament of Champions, which features winners from 2011 and is the first event of the 2012 PGA Tour season.
abstract: Karen Crouse On Golf column notes that only 27 players, and few if any headliners, are competing in the Tournament of Champions in Hawaii, which features winners from 2011 and is the first event of the 2012 PGA Tour season.
lead_paragraph: Only 27 players — and no headliners — are competing in the Tournament of Champions, which features winners from 2011 and is the first event of the 2012 PGA Tour season.

headline.seo: PGA’s Opening Event Lacks Star Power
headline.main: Plenty of Sun, but Few Stars, on Opening Day in Hawaii
headline.print_headline: Plenty of Sun, but Few Stars, on Opening Day in Hawaii
